        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         The pet delay went in pre-Kunark, when pets were gods indeed.  Now even if you gave pets back the FS delay, they still wouldn't be all that great.</P><P>But Infernall I don't think you are right in saying that Augmentation of Death gives pets the speed of FS daggers.  Heck, I don't even think AoD + Muzzle does.  I use AoD with the monk pet a lot and he still pauses for about 1-2 seconds between each attack.  Back then with the FS dagger "bug", the 49th pet simply did not stop attacking.  The spam from the fight was ridiculous.</P><P>Mathematically speaking, FS daggers have a delay of 19, while pet normal attacks have a delay of 30 (I believe).  Before Kunark we had one pet buff spell: Augment Death.  Augment Death raises pet attack speed by a max of 55%.  Augmentation of Death, only 65%.  Muzzle of Mardu gives ~10-15% increase in attack speed.  If you add it up, that means AoD + Muzzle gives (let's take the max) 80% attack speed, while Augment gives only 55%.  30 / 1.8 gives you roughly ~16.7 delay on the pet's normal attack, which is pretty damn fast.  But 19 / 1.55 gives you ~12.3 delay on the pet's normal attack.  Roughly, that's 3/4 the minimum delay we can attain now with a mage's MoM.</P><P>Of course I could be totally off base on the delay calculation, but as far as I remember it I believe the FS dagger pets were a lot faster than our current pets.</P><P>Etadanik the Redeemed</P><P>Edited by - Etadanik Mistmorgue on 07/19/2002  12:12:02<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
