         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>&lt;--wants weapon delay back<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote><BR>you know what?<BR>&lt;--wants weapon delay back</P><P>our pets used to do damage similar to a melee around the same level...now they don't come close.  give them back weapon delay (which forces us to carry around bags of daggers) and our pets will be doing damage similar to what they used to do.</P><P>old world zones with weapon delay back they will rip shit apart, new world zones they will be balanced.  that is what happens; with new expansions you get new weapons, skills, spells and your melee/casters while balanced with the new content rip the shit out of the old content...why should pets be any different?</P><P>a 10/30 weapon used to be amazing, now a lvl 30 can easily get better.  our pets (and mage pets) are melee, and should be upgraded as melee classes are upgraded.  if a mage/necro has a pet that does decent damage, they will be much more wanted in groups since between their pet and their spells they will do more damage then another melee would...as they SHOULD.  </P><P>casters should always do more damage then melee, period.  end of story.  a mage should do more damage then a rogue...a rogue should do more damage then any other melee, but not then a caster.  casters sacrafice HP/AC and weakness in lower levels to shine in the higher levels...so far i'd say wizards are the only truly balanced class.  clerics are the only class that shouldn't be doing more damage then melee (a cleric is a healer, if you made a cleric planning on doing damage...).  </P><P>i think i got off subject somewhere...*shrug* whatever.</P><P><a href="http://www.theinverselogic.com/" target="_blank"><BR>Abillister "Monkey" Abu<BR>Inverse Logic</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top 